      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-experimental-n11",
      "description": "This result summarises the most comprehensive cross-laboratory comparison performed in the study. The FEA ensemble (three independent analysts operating the same mesh under FDA, Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2, and DePuy Synthes in-house solver configurations) predicted a mean yield force of 312.6 N against an experimental mean of 308.9 N across N=11 physical constructs tested at two independent biomechanics laboratories (Laboratory A: n=6; Laboratory B: n=5). Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation was 4.1%, confirming test reproducibility. The FEA inter-analyst spread was 3.8 N (1.2%), demonstrating solver independence. Percent difference between ensemble mean and experimental mean was 1.2%; combined validation uncertainty uval was computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4 incorporating experimental measurement uncertainty (load-cell calibration ±0.5%, displacement transducer ±0.1 mm), input parameter uncertainty (titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modulus ±2 GPa, yield strength ±15 MPa), and numerical uncertainty from mesh convergence (GCI < 0.8%). The resulting E/uval ratio was 0.31, substantially below the 1.96 acceptance threshold, providing high confidence that the FEA framework accurately captures yield behaviour. This result is the primary basis for the Accepted decision.",
